content.detailedDescription: I,was at home sitting at my dining room table listening to music and playing my guitar.My dining room windows happen to be large clear glass windowed doors and it was a bright sunny day.I live in the laurel heights section of san francisco.(which by the way was the largest cemetary in sf a hundred years ago)the building i reside in is situated on a hill it is a six apt complex.My dining room windows face west, we live on the 2nd floor and from this vantage point we can see the pacific ocean on the horizon.I have to say before i continue that i would not have sub mitted this report if it were not for another incident that occured the evening of that day.Incident #1  i was sitting at my dining room table looking out my windowed doors west over the rooftops towards the ocean.I happened to have with me at that moment a pair of 10/50 binoculars which i somtimes use to stargaze or babe watch,i spotted somthing with my naked eye reflecting sunlight maybe 200 feet above the rooftops it was traveling directly west.That is when i picked up my binoculars and what i saw was a metallic ball or sphere moving very fast for about 2 seconds,then it suddenly and abrubtly turned south and dissapeared.Estimate the object was about 1 1/2 miles from my position.My brother also seen the object but without binoculars. incident#2 that evening a little after twilight,standing with my back to that same window,talking to my brother who was washing dishes in the kitchen,i turned to face the window and floating outside the window directly in front of me there was what appeared to be alarge round dark peridot green (maybe 5 ft in diameter)bubble, watery window or portal,it disappeared, blinked out the moment i looked at it.Thats my report.What i witnessed and how to explain it  i will leave that up to you.Please let me know if anyone had a similar experience  thank,you.
content.summary: Witnessed two sightings on the same day within an 8 hour period.
A small glowing (yellow middle-orange outer) circle

content.summary: A string of 9 stars traveled north to south

content.detailedDescription:
This is going to sound a bit odd.  ok, alot odd.  i was traveling north on rt.1 last night at about 9 pm in north kingstown just past oak hill road but south of the exeter exit, when i saw what looked like two very bright lights on the west side of the road (about 100 or so yards off the to the north and west.  as i approached, i realized the lights were standing still.  i slowed way down in my right lane to get a better look because as i passed the bright white lights, there were about ten neon blue strips of lights in triangular and pentagon shapes just hanging there in mid air above the trees but back into the woods.  i started to pull off the road to get a better look but i was a) shocked at what i saw and had a little bit of fear b) concerned that the cars behind me would be staring at the same thing and would rear-end my car instead of watching the road and c)i didn't want to be late to pick up my daughter from the movies in warwick.  as a result i only got a 15-20 second close look at this "thing".  i found it odd that only about 2-300 yards away there was the usual police officer parked on the south side of the road looking for speeders and he obviously didn't see anything (but he was facing north looking for the cars.  i went back with my daughter hoping it was still there and that there was a logical explaination but there was nothing there when my daughter and i returned about 9:55pm.  anyway, i was wondering if any of the other drivers reported anything to explain this very unusual phenomena.

p.S.- i'm a physician with a scientific background.  this souds as odd to me as it probably does to you.
you may contact me on my cell at 401-623-6164 if you have any questions or info for me.

thanks,

dr. jay korsen
content.summary: Very odd lights about 200 yards from the road in north kingstown

content.detailedDescription: While watching tv i fought the urge to fall asleep and a  paralizing feeling. i was startled awake by the tv going blank. my pregnant wife and son were asleep on the couch next to me i tried to wake them up and could not. i looked out side and noticed the street light also was out, which is not charicteristic of a normal power outage. i felt strangely light and my hair was standing on end.I bitterly fought a paralizing feeling in my arms and legs but i managed to break free and get up. i went outside to the deck, looked up and saw a dark rectangular object blocking out the stars. i was awe struck. there were no lights, and after my eyes adjusted i could see what appeared to be faint illuminated port holes around the edge of the craft. i felt like i was almost weightless and my hair was standing on end. it appeared to be aproximatly a half a mile high and the size of an aircraft carrier. it slowly headed north and disapeared behind the mesa. once it had gone the lights came back on and everything returned to normal.
content.summary: Awoke to power outage, went out side and saw a wrectangular shape silowetted againsed the stars.

content.summary: Sationary light appears next to jet for 5 seconds over jackson michigan.

content.detailedDescription: Dark night, looked like the 2 vertical bars of light were on the wing tips of a plane only they wern't. silent. fairly slow. they flew out to the horizon and the bar on right  moved left & merged into  bar on left and flew on as one bar. shortly thereafter the right bar  moved back to its original position to the right and they flew on out of sight after making an oblique left turn. saw nothing connecting the 2 bars. the small "strobelike" lights that ran top to bottom of  the 2 bars blinked very fast but in no apparent sequence, not 1,2,3,4 etc. but like 1,8,6,3,7 etc. couldn't tell if it were 2 objects or just 1. appeared quite low but can't estimate altitude or size. impression  was it [they] were large. bars looked dim, "strobes" looked bright. what did i see???   i was awe struck!
content.summary: 2 bars of light studded w/small blinking lights.Vertical,silent .Blend into 1, then separate .

content.detailedDescription: On aug. 13, 2005, i came home from viewing 'alien vs. predator' and was smoking on my back porch.  i remember the date because it was the movie's opening night.  i didn't have my porch light on, and, i was looking to my right at my neighbors yard when something caught my eye in the sky.  when i looked up, the object would have been at approximately 2 o'clock and highly visible against a deep dark night sky.  the moment that i looked at it, it sped with ungodly speed horizontally across the sky to this large, thick, white cloud that was approximately located at 12 o'clock.  the object was cigar shaped and it was pure white.  it was the brightest thing i've ever seen, yet, it didn't hurt my eyes for the split second that i saw it.  it's speed was unbelieveable.  there was no noise from the sky whatsoever.  i knew it was something that shouldn't have done what it did by that superfast speed with which it moved.  i was stunned there for a moment.  i'm still quite stunned when i think about it.  it was something that i could not explain.  and it's funny, because i've always thought there was something or someone else out there and wished i had been one of those people that got a glimpse of something in the sky.  yet, when i found myself wanting to share the experience, i found that i was very tentative about it.  on the night it happened, i just went back inside and thought about it even though i wanted to run and tell everyone what i had seen.
content.summary: Clear sky, few clouds, bright white object caught my eye then shot horizontally across the sky behind a large cloud

content.detailedDescription:
1.  backyard of house.
2.  i had been inside at the computer when i decided to  check on dogs who were barking unusually loud and long time in yard.  they just would not stop wailing.  something was wrong.
3.  i thought the object was a ufo.  it was like no other aircraft i have ever seen or believed could fly.
4.  the object that i saw looked like a typical "1950's ufo" as seen on t.V.  it was a grey or silver metalic-looking disc that made no sound and hovered in the sky low over house and seemed to lift up later and soar in a straight path over the neighborhood.
5.  i was very perplexed.  i was seeing a disc hover and move with ease over the houses.  my grandmother had seen it hover over the house as she was in the yard before me and even witnessed it approach.  when i got out, i could clearly see the object, but it was then flying in the air in the street by our house and then over the neighbor's house across the street.
6.  i lost sight of the object as it continued its trajectory and seemed to appear and reapear and then vanish.  i thought maybe it was due to slight clouds in the distance.  i would clearly see it in the distance, and then it would vanish and reapear until it finally disapeared from my sight.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering

i was sky-watching about 3.15pm pst today.  at 
3.22 pm, i saw a 'brush-stroke-like' part of the sky turn a slightly lighter color of blue, 
and then a white sphere appeared to 'fall out' 
of that brush-stroke.  i 
can't explain it any other way.  it just fell 
out, and hung there for seven 
minutes, until 3.29 pm. the brush-stroke was 
horizontal relative to the 
horizon, and the object fell out, or maybe

after 7 minutes, the white sphere appeared to get

content.detailedDescription: I was in the house, watching tv alone at night, late. i got a mental message to go outside and look at something. i thought that was weird, but after a few minutes, i went out. i was leaning against our barn, looking across a field. there's a spooky woods over there. i was looking across a corn field. this is a rural setting; no immediate neighbors. i was wondering why i was standing there, looking, but kept at it. suddenly, a purple object appeared about 1/2 mile away. it was beautifully purple, amethyst, lovely in color. the first object looked like a left eye shape, pointed on the inside. it seemed to pulse with energy, some huge energy, something out of this world in power. i knew it was 'looking' at me, showing itself off, showing me it was there. as i watched it, it stayed where it was, pulsing. then the other side of the eyes appeared, the right side appeared just like the first one did. now i could see two purple eye shaped things, as big as ships, 'looking' at me. it stayed that way, pulsing with superhuman strength, for about two minutes. then the side that appeared second slowly diseappeared as it had appeared, followed by the first shape. they had trouble controlling the huge amount of power they had inside, or so it seemed. i could tell they had the energy to travel through universes. i saw into another dimension for some strange reason. this appearance has been haunting me ever since. this house is out in the middle of nowhere and very old, seeming to be haunted. i used to be very sure there wasn't anything to fear here, but now i'm not so sure. i want to see this again and can feel something out of this world in the atmosphere. i can't wait for the weather to warm up so i can look at that spot every night. hopefully, i'll see it again. thanks for reading this. joan williamson
content.summary: Saw two purple objects in sky

content.detailedDescription:
I am unsure of the exact date and time because it was some years ago.  it was a late summer night, approximately 10pm-11pm.  i had just got off the bus with my friend as we returned from the summer fair.  the walk was a few blocks from the stop to the house.  

at one point we were crossing the street in a northern direction.  just before we reached the other side i happened to glance up and immediately saw a star much brighter than the others moving at a moderate speed.  it sort of looked like a dot on an old arcade machine in how it dragged a tail.  but it didnt have a tail.  it was like the light didnt dissipate immediately around the star.  i'm not sure how to describe that aspect of it.

i was looking at the sky at an angle that put the houses in front of us just out of view.  the star appeared to be moving northwest.  then, as if it knew it was seen, it switched to a northeastern direction at a sharp angle and a faster speed.  then it streaked across the sky and disappeared. (well a small piece of the sky)

when it zipped off, it wasn't like star trek where the space ship gets warp speed and flashes away.  it was like it increased speed continually and simply dissapeared.  this all happened in under 10 seconds.  the time it took to swith direction and zip off must have been under a second.

now i wouldnt have reported this if my friend hadnt seen it as well.  i remember that after seeing it and almost tripping on the curb we were both silent for a few moments.  i got excited but i wasn't sure if i should mention it because he might not have seen it, so i said,  "did you see that?"  he said he did and that he was wondering if i saw it too.  we had a good laugh about how we saw a spaceship.

at the time that i saw it i thought it was a satellite, but oddly bright.  it was odd because the light wasnt flashing or pulsating like a star.  it was solid.  i see satellites all the time in the sky when its clear enough here.  i quickly changed my mind when it took off like it did.
content.summary: Bright light moves slowly, changes direction, then zips off fast

content.detailedDescription: Every day i walk around my horse pasture (5 acres) with my dog. there is always lots of air traffic almost every day. i carry my camera with me and take pictures when things look interesting to me in the sky. a week does not pass that i don't catch something anomalous in one or several of the photos. i am sending the untouched original and an enhanced photo. the camera was pointed in a nne direction. the atlantic ocean is about one mile from where i took the photo. there were an unusual amount of chemtrails being laid when i took the photo.
content.summary: I was taking pictures of lots of contrails and chemtrails and caught this object in one of the photos
